 Security operatives from the police, Department of State Services (DSS) and Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) Tuesday morning laid siege to the residences of the Senate President Bukola Saraki and that of the Deputy Senate President Ike Ekweremadu in Abuja. THISDAY was informed that the security  operatives blocked the convoy of the Senate President near his home on Lake Chad Street in the Maitama area of the Federal Capital Territory. Sources claimed that Saraki was on his way to honour the police invitation by 8am Tuesday over the April 5 Offa Bank Robbery in Kwara State. Sources said before 8am on Tuesday, the security  operatives were seen blocking the convoy of Saraki thereby preventing him from coming out of his home. Prior to this, at around 7.20 am, the combined forces of police, DSS and EFCC had besieged the residence of  Deputy Senate President Ekweremadu in Apo, Abuja. No reason has been given by authorities for the action of the security agencies. Details later…